   358	
   359	The cap exists so a runaway experiment doesn't exhaust the
   360	operator's browser. Two distinct totals matter:
   361	
   362	- The full-log size (`total`) — observability into "how big is
   363	  this experiment's history?".
   364	- The filtered-list size (after `?type=`) — observability into
   365	  "how many of these events match my filter?".
   366	
   367	Both render. The natural index is stable per event regardless of
   368	filter, so an operator copy-pasting "event #4711" can reproduce
   369	the position deterministically across reloads.
