   371	### §A.7 Work-ref GC
   372	
   373	`GET /admin/work-refs/`:
   374	
   375	- When `app.state.repo is None`: render an explanatory placeholder
   376	  ("work-ref GC requires `--repo-path`; restart the web-ui with
   377	  the flag if you want to manage refs from this UI").
   378	- When `repo` is set: call `repo.list_refs("refs/heads/work/*")`
   379	  and classify each ref **by its name**, not by its current SHA.
   380	  The canonical ref naming pinned by the implementer module is
   381	  `refs/heads/work/<slug>-<trial_id>` (see
   382	  `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/implementer.py:69`
   383	  and the `slug` regex `^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$` in
   384	  `spec/v0/02-data-model.md` §5.1). Classification rule:
   385	
   386	  1. Strip the `refs/heads/work/` prefix; split on the **last**
   387	     `-` to get `(slug, trial_id)` candidates. (`trial_id` is
   388	     opaque per `02-data-model.md` §7.1; the slug is already
   389	     constrained to a-z/0-9/`-`, so the rightmost `-` is the only
   390	     reliable boundary.)
   391	  2. Look up `trial = store.read_trial(trial_id)`. Three outcomes:
   392	     - **Trial exists** and `trial.status` is terminal-and-handled
   393	       (`error`, `eval_error`, or `success` with `trial_commit_sha`
   394	       set) **and** the ref's current SHA equals
   395	       `trial.commit_sha` → **GC-eligible**. Show a delete button.
   396	     - **Trial exists** but is `starting`, or is `success` without
   397	       `trial_commit_sha` (integrator hasn't promoted yet), or the
   398	       ref's SHA does **not** match `trial.commit_sha` →
   399	       **Not eligible**. List the reason; no delete button. The
   400	       SHA-mismatch case is the dangerous one — it means a third
   401	       party rewrote the work branch and the operator should
   402	       investigate before deleting.
   403	     - **Trial does not exist** (the parsed `trial_id` resolves
   404	       to no trial) → **Orphan**. Most likely a leftover from a
   405	       Pre-Phase-1 ref-collision retry that succeeded on a different
   406	       name, or a manual `git update-ref` outside the system.
   407	       Show a delete button + "no trial owns this ref" warning.
   408	     - **Ref name does not parse** (no `-`, or empty slug or
   409	       trial_id segment) → list as **Unparseable**. No delete
   410	       button. The operator can clean these up via `git` directly
   411	       if they know what they are.
   412	
   413	  This trial-id-from-name discipline is the trust boundary: a SHA
   414	  collision between two trials, or a manual ref rewrite, cannot
   415	  cause us to associate a ref with the wrong trial. The SHA check
   416	  remains as the eligibility predicate for the parsed-and-known
   417	  case.
   418	
   419	`POST /admin/work-refs/delete`:
   420	
   421	- Form body has `ref_name` (e.g. `refs/heads/work/slug-T-7`) +
   422	  CSRF.
   423	- Validate `ref_name` matches `^refs/heads/work/[A-Za-z0-9_\-/.]+$`
   424	  and that the path's `work/<slug>-<trial_id>` subpath does not
   425	  contain `..` or path-separator escapes. **Critical**: any value
   426	  not matching the regex (in particular anything starting with
   427	  `refs/heads/trial/`, `refs/tags/*`, `HEAD`, or relative refs)
   428	  → 303 → `/admin/work-refs/?error=invalid-ref-name`. The regex
   429	  is the trust boundary; we do not concatenate user input into a
   430	  git plumbing command without it.

