   529	  Auth remains the chunk-9 cookie + sign-in form.
   530	
   531	## §F Security boundaries
   532	
   533	| Surface | Trust boundary |
   534	|---|---|
   535	| `/admin/*` GET | Signed-in cookie required; 303 → `/signin` otherwise |
   536	| `/admin/*` POST | Signed-in cookie + CSRF token both required |
   537	| `?limit=` / `?kind=` / `?state=` | Coerced + clamped at parse time; no echo into HTML |
   538	| `?error=…` banner | Looked up in a closed dict; no arbitrary text echo |
   539	| `ref_name` POST | Regex-validated to `^refs/heads/work/...$` + path-traversal check |
   540	| `delete_ref` | CAS via `expected_old_sha` from the **request-time** read, not the POST body |
   541	| Trial / proposal description | Jinja autoescape (same as evaluator page) |
   542	| Trial / proposal artifacts_uri | Same `_read_inline_artifact` envelope as chunks 9c/9d |
   543	| Trial / proposal artifacts_uri href | Same scheme allowlist (`http`/`https`/`file` only) |
   544	
   545	The `expected_old_sha` source matters: we read the ref SHA at the
   546	GET-time render and stash it in a hidden form field, but the POST
   547	handler **does not trust the form's hidden field** — it does its
   548	own fresh `list_refs("refs/heads/work/<name>")` lookup, uses *that*
   549	SHA as `expected_old_sha`, and only then calls `delete_ref`. The
   550	hidden field is an optimization that lets us show a stale-state
   551	banner ("the ref changed since you loaded the page") earlier; the
   552	authoritative read is server-side.
   553	
   554	## §G Errors
   555	
   556	`/admin/*` routes catch:
   557	
   558	- `IllegalTransition` (storage-domain) on reclaim → banner.
   559	- `NotFound` (from `eden_storage.errors` and re-raised by the
   560	  `eden_wire` `StoreClient` for HTTP 404 problem+json responses) on
   561	  every detail-route read (`store.read_task`, `read_trial`,
   562	  `read_proposal`). The existing `@app.exception_handler(404)` in
   563	  `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/app.py:90` only catches
   564	  HTTP 404 *responses* — it does not catch raised
   565	  `eden_storage.NotFound` / `eden_wire.NotFound` exceptions. Chunk
   566	  9e adds an explicit handler in `make_app`:
   567	
   568	  ```python
   569	  from eden_storage.errors import NotFound as StorageNotFound
   570	
   571	  @app.exception_handler(StorageNotFound)
   572	  async def _storage_not_found(request, exc):
   573	      return templates.TemplateResponse(
   574	          request, "_error.html",
   575	          {"title": "Not found", "message": str(exc)},
   576	          status_code=404,
   577	      )
   578	  ```
   579	
   580	  Routes raise it implicitly via the `Store` calls; one app-wide
   581	  handler covers every `/admin/*/<id>/` detail route plus any
   582	  similar use elsewhere in the UI. The wire-side `NotFound` and
   583	  the storage-side `NotFound` are the same exception class
   584	  (`eden_storage.errors.NotFound`, re-raised by `StoreClient`),
   585	  so a single handler suffices.
   586	
   587	- `GitError` on `list_refs` / `delete_ref` → re-raise as a 5xx
   588	  via FastAPI's default; the operator sees the standard error
   589	  page. Logging captures the git stderr.
   590	- Transport-shaped `Exception` from `StoreClient` on every read
   591	  *and* write call (per `feedback_impl_review_lenses.md` lens 11):
   592	  surfaces a `?error=transport` banner on actions; renders an
   593	  inline "transport failure; refresh to retry" placeholder on
   594	  read views.
   595	
